1
00:02:54,314 --> 00:02:56,172
- Calm down.
- Hey, fuck you!

2
00:02:57,270 --> 00:03:00,411
- Calm down.
- Fuck you!

3
00:03:14,201 --> 00:03:16,443
It's like his chute
didn't open.

4
00:03:36,755 --> 00:03:39,015
- Single shooter!
- How do you know?

5
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:05,042
Please, stop doing that!

6
00:04:10,872 --> 00:04:13,328
You're shooting
at the wrong people.

7
00:04:14,659 --> 00:04:16,060
How do I know?

8
00:04:17,393 --> 00:04:20,550
Because otherwise, we wouldn't be
having this conversation.

9
00:04:30,014 --> 00:04:31,351
Alright.

10
00:04:32,042 --> 00:04:34,060
You want to show me
the right ones?

11
00:04:38,453 --> 00:04:42,276
Nikolai.
I mean... I'm Nikolai.

12
00:04:46,461 --> 00:04:48,974
What's the last thing
you remember, Nikolai?

13
00:04:50,029 --> 00:04:52,863
War.
Yeah.

14
00:04:52,863 --> 00:04:55,149
I was at the Chechnya.

15
00:04:55,149 --> 00:04:56,960
And then there was a light.

16
00:04:57,618 --> 00:04:59,902
Then I...

17
00:04:59,902 --> 00:05:00,862
Then I woke up
and I was...

18
00:05:00,862 --> 00:05:02,580
Falling.

19
00:05:03,501 --> 00:05:06,581
Yeah, same thing.
I was in Baja.

20
00:05:06,581 --> 00:05:09,976
And then, there was a light.
And then, "chinga"!

21
00:05:16,771 --> 00:05:18,982
Okay.

22
00:05:18,982 --> 00:05:20,498
Where are we now?

23
00:05:22,561 --> 00:05:24,466
Maybe she knows.

24
00:05:26,373 --> 00:05:27,660
Shit.

25
00:05:33,206 --> 00:05:34,934
You want to lower
the weapon?

26
00:05:37,555 --> 00:05:41,482
I've never seen this jungle.
And I've seen most.

27
00:05:43,086 --> 00:05:46,610
Alright. You think that's Asia?
Maybe Africa?

28
00:05:46,610 --> 00:05:49,058
Too hot for this time of year.

29
00:05:49,058 --> 00:05:50,839
And the topography
is all wrong.

30
00:05:51,915 --> 00:05:53,292
Amazon, maybe.

31
00:05:54,274 --> 00:05:56,480
I saw more parachutes.

32
00:05:57,671 --> 00:06:00,245
- Which way?
- Why?

33
00:06:05,309 --> 00:06:08,772
So I can figure out who
threw me out of a fucking airplane.

34
00:06:16,884 --> 00:06:18,775
What the fuck?
Where she goes?

35
00:06:19,937 --> 00:06:22,357
Bullshit,
If we listen to this...

36
00:06:22,357 --> 00:06:24,877
Alright,
let's take a fucking look.

37
00:06:33,675 --> 00:06:35,416
Fuck.

38
00:07:18,357 --> 00:07:20,292
Do you remember a plane?

39
00:07:23,005 --> 00:07:26,512
I woke up in free fall.
You?

40
00:07:27,659 --> 00:07:29,270
The same.

41
00:07:30,387 --> 00:07:32,427
You're IDF?

42
00:07:32,427 --> 00:07:35,162
Yeah.
You've been in the service?

43
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:38,312
Not exactly.

44
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,527
Motherfucker!

45
00:07:41,777 --> 00:07:43,598
Move you motherfucker!

46
00:08:00,754 --> 00:08:03,151
- You with him?
- No.

47
00:08:09,073 --> 00:08:11,153
Then why don't you mind
your own fucking business?

48
00:08:12,271 --> 00:08:14,206
We have bigger problems
right now.

49
00:08:14,764 --> 00:08:18,996
Okay, boss.
Whatever you say.

50
00:08:21,341 --> 00:08:24,208
I will finish
what you started.

51
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:32,245
Strength in numbers, huh?

52
00:08:32,664 --> 00:08:35,289
- Stuff like that.
- Yeah...

53
00:08:35,289 --> 00:08:37,855
Maybe we should get that guy
hanging in the tree.

54
00:08:37,855 --> 00:08:41,886
Help me! Fuck!

55
00:08:41,886 --> 00:08:45,218
Help me!
Somebody!

56
00:08:47,702 --> 00:08:49,255
Help!

57
00:08:50,514 --> 00:08:52,089
Hello?

58
00:08:52,089 --> 00:08:54,720
I'm strapped in a parachute
in a fucking tree!

59
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:58,418
- Why don't you shut the fuck up?
- Oh, thank God!

60
00:08:58,738 --> 00:08:59,961
I think I can...

61
00:08:59,961 --> 00:09:02,071
Stop moving,
you are breaking the branch.

62
00:09:02,797 --> 00:09:04,531
Do you have anything
to cut yourself down with?

63
00:09:04,531 --> 00:09:06,372
Why would it...?
No, I dont.

64
00:09:06,643 --> 00:09:08,286
Look. If we can get him broke
from one of the chute.

65
00:09:08,286 --> 00:09:09,885
Do something!

66
00:09:14,935 --> 00:09:17,529
- Help!
- Taking too long.

67
00:09:17,529 --> 00:09:18,875
Help!

68
00:09:25,488 --> 00:09:28,812
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm a doctor...

69
00:09:29,858 --> 00:09:31,681
I was on my way to work.

70
00:09:34,012 --> 00:09:36,267
Can someone please
just tell me...

71
00:09:38,262 --> 00:09:40,851
what the fuck is going on here?

72
00:09:50,070 --> 00:09:54,870
{SALMAN}

73
00:10:09,207 --> 00:10:11,682
Your ass is awesome.

74
00:10:21,605 --> 00:10:23,142
Look.

75
00:10:28,768 --> 00:10:31,387
Hot Damn!
Who the hell is this guy?

76
00:10:47,735 --> 00:10:49,974
What the hell is that?

77
00:11:00,071 --> 00:11:01,942
Who would do this?

78
00:11:01,942 --> 00:11:05,689
Whoever they are,
they take trophies.

79
00:11:06,714 --> 00:11:10,494
In my culture,
the warrior with the greatest trophies...

80
00:11:10,494 --> 00:11:14,091
- command the most respect.
- Whatever.

81
00:11:16,308 --> 00:11:17,578
It's a test.

82
00:11:18,784 --> 00:11:21,162
To see how we do
under pressure.

83
00:11:21,915 --> 00:11:25,303
If this were a test,
you'd all be military.

84
00:11:25,303 --> 00:11:28,321
Total strangers,
Live rounds.

85
00:11:29,194 --> 00:11:31,205
This is something else.

86
00:11:31,205 --> 00:11:35,490
Maybe it's ransom.
Back in Tijuana,

87
00:11:35,490 --> 00:11:39,559
we kidnap you,
put you in an oil drum.

88
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:42,702
If the ransom not paid...

89
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:44,879
We light you on fire.

90
00:11:44,879 --> 00:11:46,811
I hear these stories,

91
00:11:46,811 --> 00:11:49,477
about these experiments
they roll on Cons.

92
00:11:49,477 --> 00:11:52,756
They stick drugs in your food,
and sit back and watch what happens.

93
00:11:52,756 --> 00:11:55,237
It's not drugs.

94
00:11:55,237 --> 00:11:58,672
If there was a psychotropic compound,
we'd be feeling the residual side effects,

95
00:11:58,672 --> 00:12:01,909
Loss of motor skills,
blurry vision...

96
00:12:03,034 --> 00:12:06,947
and if it was a behavioral experiment,
I mean, there'd...

97
00:12:06,947 --> 00:12:08,962
be a point.

98
00:12:11,051 --> 00:12:13,358
What if we are dead.

99
00:12:19,037 --> 00:12:22,608
- I was gonna be executed in two days.
- And I was in combat.

100
00:12:23,587 --> 00:12:25,482
So was I.

101
00:12:26,788 --> 00:12:28,719
This is Hell.

102
00:12:28,719 --> 00:12:31,798
Last time I looked you didn't
need a parachute to get there.

103
00:12:32,921 --> 00:12:36,315
But it doesn't matter
what happened, or why.

104
00:12:36,315 --> 00:12:38,598
We're here...

105
00:12:38,598 --> 00:12:40,730
the only question is...

106
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:42,857
How do we get out?

107
00:12:44,368 --> 00:12:46,002
Where are you going?

108
00:12:46,609 --> 00:12:50,476
- To high ground.
- We need to stick together.

109
00:12:52,168 --> 00:12:54,615
Then you should follow me.

110
00:13:01,178 --> 00:13:05,978
{SALMAN}

111
00:13:30,266 --> 00:13:32,069
Yeah, I wouldn't do that.

112
00:13:40,146 --> 00:13:41,624
Yep.

113
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:47,175
Archaefructus liaoningensis.
That is really, really poisonous.

114
00:13:48,799 --> 00:13:52,694
Wouldn't take more than one scratch,
cause total paralysis.

115
00:13:55,243 --> 00:13:57,082
Thank you.

116
00:13:57,082 --> 00:13:59,349
I will watch for you out here.

117
00:14:02,301 --> 00:14:04,278
You made a buddy.

118
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:13,776
Hey.

119
00:14:14,928 --> 00:14:16,744
We need to rest.

120
00:14:17,762 --> 00:14:19,570
So rest.

121
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,640
You look like
you could use it too.

122
00:14:26,114 --> 00:14:27,974
You got a name?

123
00:14:31,323 --> 00:14:33,037
Look...

124
00:14:33,037 --> 00:14:36,358
I'm sorry. You want to play
scout leader? Great.

125
00:14:36,358 --> 00:14:38,596
Now you gonna follow me?
Fine.

126
00:14:39,055 --> 00:14:41,086
But I'm not doing this...

127
00:14:41,788 --> 00:14:43,861
I'm better on my own.

128
00:14:45,242 --> 00:14:47,741
Want to see something
fucked up?

129
00:15:08,045 --> 00:15:10,762
Well, between that
and the sun...

130
00:15:11,545 --> 00:15:15,216
- I'd say we have a real problem.
- What about the sun?

131
00:15:16,758 --> 00:15:19,358
It hasn't moved
since we got here.

132
00:15:24,710 --> 00:15:27,163
What do you think
is really going on?

133
00:15:30,716 --> 00:15:32,523
What do I think?

134
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:38,346
Spetznatz Alpha Group,

135
00:15:38,815 --> 00:15:41,615
Los Zetas cartel enforcer,

136
00:15:42,121 --> 00:15:46,786
R.U.F. that's a death squad
from Sierra Leone,

137
00:15:46,786 --> 00:15:49,268
Yakuza in the Dawokei,

138
00:15:49,268 --> 00:15:51,807
the F.B.I.'s Most Wanted,

139
00:15:52,062 --> 00:15:54,651
and... him.

140
00:15:56,254 --> 00:15:59,296
They're all heavy-hitters,
he doesn't belong.

141
00:16:00,671 --> 00:16:02,455
Belong to what?

142
00:16:04,780 --> 00:16:07,367
Well, I'd say
we were chosen.

143
00:16:12,738 --> 00:16:14,824
What about you?

144
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:18,008
What about me?

145
00:16:20,014 --> 00:16:23,831
You know the jungle,
all the players...

146
00:16:25,498 --> 00:16:29,422
I'm guessing ex-military,
black-ops,

147
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:33,358
- probably a mercenary.
- You got a problem with that?

148
00:16:36,886 --> 00:16:38,851
Not at the moment.

149
00:16:40,388 --> 00:16:42,371
Good.

150
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:52,306
{SALMAN}

151
00:18:19,931 --> 00:18:22,289
Something
was dropped here.

152
00:18:23,153 --> 00:18:25,059
Same as us.

153
00:18:26,862 --> 00:18:29,105
Not the same as us.

154
00:18:34,819 --> 00:18:36,909
You said we were chosen.

155
00:18:39,262 --> 00:18:41,689
Chosen for what?

156
00:18:43,473 --> 00:18:45,696
Oh, shit.

157
00:19:16,932 --> 00:19:19,130
Looking good there, boss.

158
00:19:25,924 --> 00:19:27,375
Look out! Step!

159
00:19:51,618 --> 00:19:52,770
Help!

160
00:20:33,755 --> 00:20:37,468
- 12 o'clock. 110 meters.
- Take him! Take him!

161
00:20:37,468 --> 00:20:39,224
We don't have to.

162
00:20:41,593 --> 00:20:43,269
He left.

163
00:20:50,476 --> 00:20:52,690
We triggered a dead man's trap.

164
00:20:55,475 --> 00:20:57,315
It's two weeks.

165
00:20:57,315 --> 00:21:00,013
Judging from
the rate of decomposition.

166
00:21:01,023 --> 00:21:03,147
He took up a position here.

167
00:21:06,046 --> 00:21:08,290
shooting in all directions.

168
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:11,059
This was a last stand.

169
00:21:18,511 --> 00:21:20,544
United States Special Forces.

170
00:21:21,286 --> 00:21:24,480
This is strange.
He's supposed to be...

171
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:26,478
deployed in Afghanistan.

172
00:21:27,113 --> 00:21:29,460
What's he doing here
setting traps for us?

173
00:21:29,606 --> 00:21:31,790
They weren't meant for us.

174
00:21:32,577 --> 00:21:34,508
He was hunting something else...

175
00:21:35,034 --> 00:21:38,153
- Something a lot bigger.
- Bigger?

176
00:21:39,306 --> 00:21:41,201
The trunk was a dead-fall.

177
00:21:41,201 --> 00:21:42,468
The rule of thumb
with a dead-fall,

178
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:45,636
is that you set the weight five times
that of the target animal.

179
00:21:46,524 --> 00:21:49,217
Whatever it was,
it got through the trip-wires.

180
00:21:49,217 --> 00:21:50,907
And did this.

181
00:21:55,922 --> 00:21:57,671
Let's move.

182
00:22:18,374 --> 00:22:19,768
What is it?

183
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:22,828
<i>What is it?</i>

184
00:22:30,832 --> 00:22:32,280
Nothing.

185
00:22:43,087 --> 00:22:48,235
<i>What is it?
Nothing.</i>

186
00:22:51,777 --> 00:22:56,578
{SALMAN}

187
00:23:54,908 --> 00:23:57,787
We're gonna need
a new plan.

188
00:24:16,579 --> 00:24:18,378
Hey, where are we going?

189
00:24:18,378 --> 00:24:22,404
Someone put us on this rock,
there's gotta be a way off it.

190
00:24:24,207 --> 00:24:26,465
Ah!
What the fuck?

191
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:32,682
Hey, you know what?
Fuck this!

192
00:24:33,358 --> 00:24:36,281
This is bullshit, man.
I want a gun!

193
00:24:36,922 --> 00:24:38,941
Come man. You got
two mother fucking guns, man!

194
00:24:38,941 --> 00:24:40,744
Somebody give me a gun!

195
00:24:41,425 --> 00:24:44,357
Come on Russian,
you got a big fucking gun!

196
00:24:49,444 --> 00:24:52,574
Come on man,
give me a gun.

197
00:24:53,824 --> 00:24:56,356
Give me a gun, right now!

198
00:24:57,394 --> 00:24:58,854
Give me a gun.

199
00:25:05,482 --> 00:25:09,093
I'm ready to die.

200
00:25:09,093 --> 00:25:11,387
Are you?

201
00:25:18,204 --> 00:25:23,004
{SALMAN}

202
00:26:28,154 --> 00:26:29,550
Help!

203
00:27:02,740 --> 00:27:04,182
Help!

204
00:27:06,580 --> 00:27:09,161
Fuck you!

205
00:27:15,926 --> 00:27:18,164
Looking good there, boss.

206
00:27:30,762 --> 00:27:34,356
Run! Run!
Come on! Climb!

207
00:27:43,789 --> 00:27:45,401
Oh, shit!

208
00:27:58,273 --> 00:27:59,775
No!

209
00:28:28,774 --> 00:28:32,133
As bad as you are...

210
00:28:32,133 --> 00:28:34,260
those things are worse.

211
00:28:41,826 --> 00:28:46,626
{SALMAN}

212
00:28:51,564 --> 00:28:54,948
Since we still eight,
they just... What? Left?

213
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,247
No.

214
00:28:57,247 --> 00:28:59,591
The whistle.

215
00:28:59,591 --> 00:29:01,435
They were called.

216
00:29:01,435 --> 00:29:03,162
Alright. Listen up!

217
00:29:03,162 --> 00:29:05,236
Everybody do a shell count.

218
00:29:06,395 --> 00:29:08,186
We've got to
conserve ammunition.

219
00:29:08,695 --> 00:29:10,707
Reload. Do it now.

220
00:29:11,016 --> 00:29:14,541
Excuse me, I'm...
just what the hell is going on here?

221
00:29:15,749 --> 00:29:17,521
We're being hunted.

222
00:29:20,326 --> 00:29:25,222
The cages, soldier,
all of us.

223
00:29:25,222 --> 00:29:27,325
All brought here
for the same purpose.

224
00:29:29,653 --> 00:29:31,821
This planet
is a game preserve.

225
00:29:33,335 --> 00:29:35,079
And we're the game.

226
00:29:38,114 --> 00:29:40,259
In case you didn't notice,

227
00:29:40,259 --> 00:29:42,330
we just got flushed out.

228
00:29:44,554 --> 00:29:46,424
They sent the dogs in.

229
00:29:46,424 --> 00:29:49,081
Just like you would
if you were stalking boar.

230
00:29:49,081 --> 00:29:51,040
Shooting quail.

231
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:53,833
They split us apart,
and they watched.

232
00:29:53,833 --> 00:29:55,567
Testing us.

233
00:30:00,848 --> 00:30:02,877
How do you know all this?

234
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:06,258
Because...

235
00:30:06,258 --> 00:30:08,320
that's what I would do.

236
00:30:10,775 --> 00:30:14,328
- Fantastic.
- Wait...

237
00:30:16,572 --> 00:30:20,765
- There are only seven of us.
- Help me!

238
00:30:30,153 --> 00:30:32,494
Help!

239
00:30:58,237 --> 00:30:59,897
Help.

240
00:31:02,275 --> 00:31:04,054
- Wait...
- What?

241
00:31:05,373 --> 00:31:07,213
It's a trap.

242
00:31:16,511 --> 00:31:19,243
Help me.

243
00:31:32,755 --> 00:31:34,703
Fuck me.

244
00:31:35,668 --> 00:31:38,338
Help.

245
00:31:41,064 --> 00:31:42,968
Wound one man.

246
00:31:44,111 --> 00:31:45,977
Make him suffer.

247
00:31:47,496 --> 00:31:49,381
Make him bleed.

248
00:31:51,986 --> 00:31:54,587
Make him call out for help.

249
00:31:54,587 --> 00:31:58,404
And set a trap,
and kill those who come.

250
00:32:01,997 --> 00:32:04,590
I know,
because I have done this.

251
00:32:06,177 --> 00:32:08,546
So we're gonna leave him here,
right?

252
00:32:09,694 --> 00:32:12,913
Come on, look at him.
He's done.

253
00:32:13,801 --> 00:32:16,801
There's nothing...
There's nothing else we can do, right?

254
00:32:17,307 --> 00:32:18,800
Right?

255
00:32:26,177 --> 00:32:27,786
We leave him.

256
00:32:28,736 --> 00:32:31,172
I can't.

257
00:32:31,172 --> 00:32:33,437
Then that's on you.

258
00:32:49,037 --> 00:32:52,644
Help me.

259
00:33:14,258 --> 00:33:17,981
Help me.

260
00:33:27,115 --> 00:33:31,388
<i>Help me. Help me.
It's a trap. It's a trap.</i>

261
00:33:34,619 --> 00:33:39,419
{SALMAN}

262
00:33:51,685 --> 00:33:54,727
What are we gonna do?

263
00:33:54,727 --> 00:33:56,955
We should go
to higher ground.

264
00:33:56,955 --> 00:33:58,692
Really?

265
00:33:58,692 --> 00:34:00,573
We're trapped
on an alien hunting planet,

266
00:34:00,573 --> 00:34:02,522
you really think
the solution is to...

267
00:34:02,522 --> 00:34:04,341
walk over?

268
00:34:07,825 --> 00:34:09,972
It wants us to run.

269
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:14,367
That's how it hunts.

270
00:34:17,260 --> 00:34:20,135
